This paper combines deep learning and heuristic search to learn complex spatial structures from sparse examples with noise. The use of deep learning models such as convolutional and sequential models suggests that this paper belongs to the cs.AI and cs.LG sub-categories. The use of a virtual table and CNN to predict the most similar complete example structure after each placement suggests that this paper also belongs to the cs.CV sub-category. The use of heuristic search algorithms suggests that this paper belongs to the cs.RO and cs.SY sub-categories. Overall, the most likely sub-categories are cs.AI and cs.LG, followed by cs.CV, cs.RO, and cs.SY.
